          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">It=E2=80=99s been a=
 frenetic four weeks for <b>Steve</b> <b>Bannon</b>. At the tail end of Oct=
ober, just before the election, the pied-piper of the MAGA movement was rel=
eased from federal prison in Connecticut in the middle of the night, 20 pou=
nds lighter after serving a four-month sentence for refusing to cooperate w=
ith a subpoena from the congressional committee investigating the January 6=
 riot. Bannon couldn=E2=80=99t follow much election news in prison, but onc=
e out, he picked up his populist crusade right where he left off. He donned=
 his Barbour jacket and went straight back into the <i>War Room</i>, his fr=
eewheeling daily show, where he urged his posse of deplorable followers to =
mobilize for <b>Donald</b> <b>Trump</b> in the final week before Election D=
ay. <br/><br/>In his first show back, Bannon peppered his Trump cheerleadin=
g with some conspiratorial
hedging=E2=80=94=E2=80=9Cthey,=E2=80=9D meaning the deep state and the Demo=
crats, were going to try to steal the election again=E2=80=94but it turned =
out he didn=E2=80=99t need to. Trump won easily. It was the kind of victory=
 that Bannon has been dreaming about for a very long time, going back to wh=
en I first met him in 2011, when he was palling around with <b>Sarah</b> <b=
>Palin</b>. Unlike Trump=E2=80=99s first victory eight years ago, his win t=
his month was unambiguous, built on a multiracial coalition of voters rejec=
ting what Bannon calls the =E2=80=9Ccredentialed class.=E2=80=9D Trump won =
by openly promising to deport illegal immigrants, stand up for U.S. workers=
 with tariffs against China, scale down America=E2=80=99s military presence=
 overseas, and root out his political enemies. MAGA in full.<br/></td>
